    "Estimate the intrinsic dimension of the count matrix, and find k archetypes that identify the hypothesized purest spots. 2.",
    "Find the N-nearest neighbors of each archetype, and construct archetypal communities.",
    "Find the most highly and differentially expressed genes for each archetypal community, and select the top n genes (default, n = 30) as the 'archetypal marker genes'. 4.",
    "If the signature gene sets are provided, align the archetypal communities to the best matched known cell types, update the signature genes by appending archetypal marker genes to the aligned cell type and recalculate the anchors. 5.",
    "If the signature gene sets are absent, apply the archetypes and their corresponding marker genes as the signatures."
